Collahuasi Copper Mine in Chile Is Not Affected by 6.2-Magnitude Temblor

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-06T13:49:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-06/collahuasi-copper-mine-in-chile-is-not-affected-by-6-2-magnitude-temblor.html
Operations at  Anglo American Plc (AAL)  and  Xstrata Plc (XTA) ’s Collahuasi copper mine, the world’s third biggest,
were not affected by a temblor that shook southern Peru and
northern Chile earlier today, Collahuasi spokesperson Bernardita
Fernandez said in a telephone interview.  The earthquake struck at 7:32 a.m. New York time and
measured 6.2 degrees on the Richter scale, according to
information posted on the website of the U.S. Geological Survey.
The temblor was located 92 kilometers (57 miles) east of the
Peruvian city of Tacna and 108 kilometers from the Chilean city
of Arica. It had a depth of 88 kilometers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
